<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="header">
            <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: February 1, 2026</p>
        </div>

        <div class="highlight">
            <p><strong>Introduction:</strong> We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
        
        <h3>1.1 Information You Provide Directly</h3>
        <p><strong>Account Information:</strong></p>
        <ul>
            <li>Name or username (if you create an account)</li>
            <li>Email address (if provided)</li>
            <li>Profile information (optional)</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p><strong>Recovery Tracking Data:</strong></p>
        <ul>
            <li>Sobriety start dates</li>
            <li>Addiction types you're tracking</li>
            <li>Daily pledge status</li>
            <li>Journal entries and notes</li>
            <li>Mood tracking data</li>
            <li>Personal goals and motivations</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="highlight">
            <p><strong>Note:</strong> We do not collect or store payment information. All subscription payments are processed through Apple's App Store.</p>
        </div>

        <h3>1.3 Health Data (HealthKit Integration)</h3>
        <p>With your explicit permission, Resara may access the following health data through Apple HealthKit:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Sleep analysis (total sleep, deep sleep, REM, core sleep)</li>
            <li>Resting heart rate</li>
            <li>Heart rate variability (HRV)</li>
            <li>Step count</li>
            <li>Active energy burned</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="important">
            <p><strong>Important - Health Data Privacy:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Health data is <strong>ONLY</strong> accessed if you explicitly grant permission</li>
                <li>Health data is <strong>stored locally on your device only</strong></li>
                <li>We <strong>DO NOT</strong> upload health data to our servers</li>
                <li>We <strong>DO NOT</strong> share health data with third parties</li>
                <li>Health data is used solely to display Bio-Sync Recovery insights</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h3>1.4 Information We Do NOT Collect</h3>
        <div class="good-news">
            <p>We do not collect:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Precise real-time location data</li>
                <li>Contacts from your device</li>
                <li>Photos or media (unless you explicitly add them)</li>
                <li>Microphone or camera data</li>
                <li>Sensitive personal information (race, religion, political views)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        
        <h3>2.1 To Provide and Improve the App</h3>
        <p>We use your information to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Create and maintain your account</li>
            <li>Track your sobriety progress</li>
            <li>Calculate statistics (days sober, money saved, time saved)</li>
            <li>Display your journal entries and notes</li>
            <li>Send you milestone notifications</li>
            <li>Provide personalized insights and analytics</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2.2 Premium Features</h3>
        <p>For Premium subscribers, we use information to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Provide AI-powered recovery coaching (processed on-device)</li>
            <li>Generate personalized motivational quotes</li>
            <li>Create advanced analytics and insights</li>
            <li>Display Bio-Sync health recovery metrics</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="highlight">
            <p><strong>Note:</strong> AI features use on-device processing through Apple Intelligence. Your personal data is NOT sent to external servers for AI processing.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>3. How We Store Your Information</h2>
        
        <h3>3.1 Local Storage</h3>
        <div class="good-news">
            <p><strong>Most data is stored locally on your device:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>All journal entries</li>
                <li>Daily pledges</li>
                <li>Personal notes and reflections</li>
                <li>Health data from HealthKit</li>
                <li>Recovery tracking statistics</li>
            </ul>
            <p>This data is stored using encrypted storage on your device and SwiftData (Apple's local database framework).</p>
        </div>

        <h3>3.2 Cloud Storage (Optional)</h3>
        <p>If you enable iCloud sync:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Your data syncs across your Apple devices</li>
            <li>Data is encrypted in transit and at rest</li>
            <li>Data is stored in your personal iCloud account</li>
            <li>We do not have access to your iCloud data</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. How We Share Your Information</h2>
        
        <div class="good-news">
            <h3>4.1 We DO NOT Sell Your Data</h3>
            <p><strong>We will NEVER sell, rent, or trade your personal information to third parties.</strong></p>
        </div>

        <h3>4.2 Service Providers</h3>
        <p>We may share limited data with trusted service providers:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Apple Services:</strong> App Store, HealthKit, Apple Intelligence, iCloud, Push Notifications</li>
            <li><strong>Analytics Services:</strong> App performance monitoring and crash reporting</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>All third-party services are required to keep your information confidential and use it only for specified purposes.</p>

        <h3>4.3 Legal Requirements</h3>
        <p>We may disclose your information if required to comply with legal obligations, protect our rights, or prevent fraud.</p>

        <h2>5. Your Privacy Rights and Choices</h2>
        
        <h3>5.1 Access and Correction</h3>
        <p>You have the right to access, correct, and update your personal information through the App's settings.</p>

        <h3>5.2 Data Deletion</h3>
        <p>You can delete your data:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Delete individual journal entries within the App</li>
            <li>Delete your entire account through App settings</li>
            <li>Request data deletion by contacting privacy@resara.app</li>
        </ul>
        
        <div class="important">
            <p><strong>Important:</strong> Deletion is permanent and cannot be undone.</p>
        </div>

        <h3>5.3 Data Portability</h3>
        <p>You can export your data:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Export journal entries as PDF (Premium feature)</li>
            <li>Request a copy of your data by contacting privacy@resara.app</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>5.4 HealthKit Permissions</h3>
        <p>You can control HealthKit access:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Grant or revoke permissions in iOS Settings → Health → Data Access & Devices</li>
            <li>Disable Bio-Sync features in App settings</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>5.5 Notifications</h3>
        <p>You can control notifications in iOS Settings or App settings.</p>

        <h2>6. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>Resara is intended for users aged 13 and older. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. Users between 13-18 should obtain parental consent before using the App.</p>

        <h2>7. Data Security</h2>
        
        <h3>7.1 Security Measures</h3>
        <p>We implement industry-standard security measures:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Encryption of data in transit (HTTPS/TLS)</li>
            <li>Encryption of data at rest on your device</li>
            <li>Secure authentication protocols</li>
            <li>Regular security audits and updates</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>7.2 Device Security</h3>
        <p>Your device security is critical:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Use a strong device passcode</li>
            <li>Enable Face ID or Touch ID</li>
            <li>Keep iOS updated</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="important">
            <p><strong>Note:</strong> While we strive to protect your data, no method of transmission or storage is 100% secure.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>8. Your Rights Under Specific Laws</h2>
        
        <h3>8.1 GDPR (European Users)</h3>
        <p>If you are in the European Economic Area, you have additional rights including:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Right to Access</li>
            <li>Right to Rectification</li>
            <li>Right to Erasure ("right to be forgotten")</li>
            <li>Right to Data Portability</li>
            <li>Right to Object</li>
            <li>Right to Withdraw Consent</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>8.2 CCPA (California Users)</h3>
        <p>California residents have rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act, including the right to know what information we collect and the right to delete your information.</p>
        
        <div class="good-news">
            <p><strong>We do not sell personal information.</strong></p>
        </div>

        <h2>13. Privacy Policy for Health Data</h2>
        
        <h3>13.1 Special Protection for Health Data</h3>
        <div class="important">
            <p>We recognize that health data is particularly sensitive and deserves special protection:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Explicit Consent Required:</strong> We only access health data with your explicit permission</li>
                <li><strong>Local Storage Only:</strong> Health data is NEVER uploaded to servers</li>
                <li><strong>No Third-Party Sharing:</strong> Health data is NEVER shared</li>
                <li><strong>No Advertising Use:</strong> Health data is NEVER used for advertising</li>
                <li><strong>User Control:</strong> You can revoke access at any time</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h3>13.5 HIPAA Disclaimer</h3>
        <div class="important">
            <p><strong>Resara is NOT a HIPAA-covered entity.</strong> We do not provide healthcare services and are not subject to HIPAA regulations. The App is a wellness tool, not a medical device.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>11. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of material changes by updating the "Last Updated" date and posting a notice in the App.</p>

        <div class="contact">
            <h2>12. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>If you have questions regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us:</p>
            <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:privacy@resara.app">privacy@resara.app</a></p>
            <p><strong>Support Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:support@resara.app">support@resara.app</a></p>
            <p><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://resara.app">https://resara.app</a></p>
            <p><strong>Response Time:</strong> We will respond to privacy inquiries within 30 days.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="footer">
            <p><strong>By using Resara, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to this Privacy Policy.</strong></p>
            <p style="margin-top: 20px;">© 2026 Resara. All rights reserved.</p>
        </div>
